4.
The DOM stands for Document Object Model and it's a interface for web documents, representing them as a tree of nodes, including elements and text. 
The DOM tree is this hierarchical representation, allowing scripts to read and manipulate the document's content, structure, and styles.

5.
XSS stands for Cross-Site Scripting and these attacks involve injecting malicious scripts into web pages that are viewed by others. 
These attacks can steal sensitive data like cookies or session tokens.
To guard against these attacks it's best to validate and sanitize input to ensure it doesn't contain executable code.
